{
  "texts": [
    "By comparing the performances on QA and VA tests, we find that most Video-LLMs experience greater performance loss on edited VA data compared to QA data, especially for GPT-4o whose performance degenerates marginally on QA questions (2.6%) but more on VA type questions (9.9%).",
    "Such a discrepancy suggests that the models are primarily exploiting spurious vision-text correspondence for answer prediction.",
    "Additionally, we extend our experiments to the recent NExT-OOD dataset (Zhang et al., 2024c).",
    "NExT-OOD is also designed to reduce candidate answer biases in NExT-QA.",
    "It aims for a balanced distribution of objects and actions in the correct and distractor an- swers, whereas our VA and QA short-cuts pertains to the video-and question-correlated candidate answers."
  ]
}